Key Match Events: Mitchell Santner took five wickets for Netherlands, contributing significantly to New Zealand's victory.
Colin Ackermann scored 69 runs for Netherlands, his highest individual score in the match.
Scott Edwards scored 30 runs for Netherlands, ending the innings with a six off Santner.
New Zealand scored 322 runs in their innings, setting a high target for Netherlands.
Pre-Game Insights: Scott Edwards (Netherlands) mentioned that they were going to bowl first due to better bowling conditions early in the day.
Tom Latham (New Zealand) said they would have preferred to bat first but acknowledged the good surface and strong bowling performance in their previous game.
Post-Match Reflections: No specific post-match reflections were mentioned in the article.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium in Hyderabad.
New Zealand won by 99 runs, securing their second win in the ICC ODI World Cup 2023.
